President Donald J. Trump and Prime Minister Shinzo Abe of Japan met at the G20 Summit in Hamburg, Germany and condemned North Korea's recent intercontinental ballistic missile launch. They agreed that North Korea poses a threat to the United States, its allies, and countries worldwide. The leaders emphasized the need for the international community to address North Korea's missile and nuclear weapons programs quickly and decisively. President Trump reaffirmed the United States' commitment to defend Japan and South Korea from any attack, using all available capabilities. They also pledged to increase efforts to unite nations in showing North Korea the consequences of its threatening actions. The leaders discussed other regional issues of mutual interest and reiterated the importance of the strong United States-Japan Alliance for peace and prosperity.